title: Energy stocks lead an early decline on Wall Street; Oil down
text: Photo: Richard Drew, AP FILE - In this Oct. 2, 2014, file photo, people pass a Wall Street subway stop, in New York's Financial District. European shares were mostly higher Monday, Oct. 19, 2015, while Chinese markets zigzagged after quarterly growth figures countered pessimism about the world's No. 2 economy. Other Asian markets ended little changed. FILE - In this Oct. 2, 2014, file photo, people pass a Wall Street... NEW YORK (AP) — Energy stocks are leading an early decline on Wall Street as the price of oil turns lower.
